This paper deals with the problem of action segmentation in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The proposed model uses a recurrent neural network architecture, which is also a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the model is evaluated on three different datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
